snippet.textDisplay: Okay, hear me out. What if Theros' Underworld suppresses your "abilities" when your "dead" you become an Returned and you forfeit them; in conclusion, Elspeth was still a Planeswalker, but her spark was placed into dormancy, hence the flash of light, her spark reigniting due to Sparks being perfectly capable of saving the owner. snippet.textDisplay: I really hate that I have gotten into this. It started with Throne of Eldraine because I love fairytales and I thought oh that's a neat idea trading cards based on those. Then I started buying cheap 4 dollar 100 card backs from the dollar store. "Ooo zombies? vampires? spirits? These undead cards are cool" cut to buying old Innstraid card backs, and Theros. Greek mythology and Eldritch horrors? Pulling me deeper and deeper until I am literally walking from work (while I am still working) to by more cheap packs. I just watch specific creatures and cards now. Trying to complete the Throne of Eldraine. I am a collector though. I don't play the game, I find it incomprehensible.
